          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Water-cooled Hafnium foil of 1 mm thickness and 1 cm",
                " diameter was irradiated for 12 hr at beam current",
                " 30 uA. Proton energy 27 MeV was adjusted at the",
                " maximum of 180Hf(n,2n)179Ta reaction cross section.",
                " A number of short-lived by-products were allowed to",
                " decay during storage time of 6 months.",
                " Approximately 1.4 ug of 179Ta was obtained and",
                " two samples were prepared by electrospraying on Al",
                " backing.",
                "- 1st having mass 3.71 nano-g, 179Ta atoms number",
                " (1.25 +- 0.02) x 10**13, diameter 8 mm, activity",
                "  (1.5 +- 0.02) x 10**5 Bq.",
                "- 2nd having mass 22.4 nano-g, 179Ta atoms number",
                " (7.52 +- 0.20) x 10**13, diameter 10 mm, activity",
                "  (9.07 +- 0.15) x 10**5 Bq"
              ]
            }
          ],
